    "title": "Himalaya Drug Company is Hiring: Quality Control Engineer (Senior)",
    "description": "Himalaya Drug Company has an exciting opening for a Quality Control Engineer at our Kochi office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Himalaya Drug Company:\nHimalaya Drug Company is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Implement 5S, Kaizen, and Six Sigma practices on the shop floor\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in Six Sigma\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in APQP\n• Proficiency in Root Cause Analysis\n• Proficiency in 5S\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Flexible working hours\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Kochi, Kerala, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Himalaya Drug Company!",
